Django Ranger Project

Django Ranger is a web application built with Django and Django REST Framework (DRF), designed to interact with an existing PostgreSQL database originally structured for a Laravel application. It exposes a set of RESTful APIs to manage and access data from pre-existing tables.

Features
Django Framework: A powerful and scalable web framework for rapid development.

Django REST Framework (DRF): Flexible and robust toolkit for building Web APIs.

PostgreSQL Integration: Connects to a pre-existing PostgreSQL database (originally from a Laravel backend).

Containerized Environment: Uses Docker and Docker Compose for easy and consistent setup.

Legacy Database Support: Models are reverse-engineered to map to existing tables like:

RESTful API: Clean and standardized API endpoints to expose the data.

Prerequisites
Ensure the following tools are installed on your machine:

Docker

Docker Compose (bundled with Docker Desktop)

Getting Started
Follow these steps to set up the project locally:

1. Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/SrinivasaRamesh48/django-ranger.git
cd django-ranger

2. Run the Application with Docker
docker-compose up --build
The API will be available at: http://localhost:8000/

